                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340703-152-off839 t18340703-152-crimeloc841"></join>. On the 2d of July I saw the prisoner in Fore-street - I am shopman to Jacob Russell, who is a <rs id="t18340703-152-viclabel842" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340703-152-victim961 t18340703-152-viclabel842"></join> - this handkerchief was at the door-post between ten and eleven o'clock - I received information - went to the door, and missed it - I saw the prisoner run round the corner into London Wall, and came up within six yards of him - he pulled the handkerchief out of his jacket or breast, and threw it into the road - I followed him, and saw him taken into custody - the witness Williams took it up in my presence - there was another person apparently concerned.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340703-152-person963">
                  JOHN 
                  WILLIAMS
               <interp inst="t18340703-152-person963" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
